Description: Fragment of neck and oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora, moderate turn. Clay fine mid-brown. Red paint. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Xenaratos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0186.29.
Acquisition name: Donated by: Sir Charles Thomas Newton (perhaps)
Donated by: Egypt Exploration Fund (perhaps, because of trimming, but not surface condition)
